                    }, 
                    "section_id": 595, 
                    "source": "Bestiary 2", 
                    "type": "ability"
                }
            ], 
            "section_id": 594, 
            "subtype": "special_abilities", 
            "type": "section"
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Cursed from birth, dhampirs result from the rare and unnatural union of vampires and humans. Although not driven to consume blood for survival as their undead progenitors are, dhampirs nonetheless know a lifelong desire for blood that nothing else can truly sate. Those who survive their early years face a life of fear and mistrust, their unnatural beauty and incredible reflexes marking them as scions of the night just as surely as their sensitivity to light. Although polluted by undeath, dhampirs do grow old and die, aging at a rate similar to elves.</p>", 
            "source": "Bestiary 2", 
            "type": "section", 
            "section_id": 596
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>Dhampirs are defined by class levels&mdash;they don't possess racial Hit Dice. All dhampirs have the following racial traits.</p>", 
            "name": "Dhampir", 
            "source": "Bestiary 2", 
            "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 2/Monsters/Dhampir/Dhampir", 
            "type": "race", 
            "section_id": 597, 
            "subtype": "monster_race", 
            "sections": [
                {
                    "body": "<p>Dhampirs are fast and seductive, but closer to death than most mortals.</p>", 
                    "source": "Bestiary 2", 
                    "type": "section", 
                    "name": "+2 Dexterity, +2 Charisma, -2 Constitution", 
                    "section_id": 598
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "<p>Low-light vision and darkvision 60 feet.</p>", 
                    "name": "Senses", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 2/Monsters/Dhampir/Dhampir/Senses", 
                    "section_id": 599, 
                    "source": "Bestiary 2", 
                    "type": "section"
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "<p>+2 racial bonus on Bluff and Perception.</p>", 
                    "name": "Manipulative", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 2/Monsters/Dhampir/Dhampir/Manipulative", 
                    "section_id": 600, 
                    "source": "Bestiary 2", 
                    "type": "section"
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "<p>Dhampirs gain a +2 racial bonus on saving throws against disease and mind-affecting effects.</p>", 
                    "name": "Undead Resistance", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 2/Monsters/Dhampir/Dhampir/Undead Resistance", 
                    "section_id": 601, 
                    "source": "Bestiary 2", 
                    "type": "section"
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "See Universal Monster Rules/Light Sensitivity</p>", 
                    "source": "Bestiary 2", 
                    "type": "link", 
                    "name": "Light Sensitivity", 
                    "section_id": 602
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "See Universal Monster Rules/Negative Energy Affinity</p>", 
                    "source": "Bestiary 2", 
                    "type": "link", 
                    "name": "Negative Energy Affinity", 
                    "section_id": 603
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "<p>A dhampir can use<i> detect undead</i> three times per day as a spell-like ability. The caster level for this ability equals the dhampir's class level.</p>", 
                    "name": "Spell-Like Ability", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 2/Monsters/Dhampir/Dhampir/Spell-Like Ability", 
